  <datafield tag="500" ind1=" " ind2=" ">
    <subfield code="a">William Lloyd Garrison wants Oliver Johnson to send him &quot;a congratulatory and farewell letter&quot; for insertion in the last issue of the Liberator. He tells Johnson how long the article should be and when he needs to have it. Garrison writes: &quot;How much, dear Oliver, I have owed you in the past for your steadfast friendship, your sound judgment, your clear vision, your hopeful spirit, your hearty co-operation, and your many acts of brotherly kindness! If in any way, or to any extent, I have been of any service to you, I shall rejoice.&quot; </subfield>
  </datafield>
